Initialize Firebase Emulators: Run the Firebase emulator initialization command in your project root.

(Command: firebase init emulators)

(Follow the prompts to select which emulators to initialize - at least Firestore, Authentication, and Storage are needed)

Start Firebase Emulators: Start the Firebase emulators.

(Command: firebase emulators:start)

(Leave this command running in a separate terminal window)

Verify Emulator UI: Open your browser and navigate to the Firebase Emulator UI to verify the emulators are running.

(URL: http://localhost:4000)

(Check that Firestore, Authentication, and Storage are listed as running)